"494","<P STYLE=margin: 0><B>REPORT OF INDEPENDENT REGISTERED PUBLIC ACCOUNTING FIRM</B></P>"
"495","<P STYLE=margin: 0>&nbsp;</P>"
"496","<P STYLE=margin: 0>Board of Directors and Shareholders<FONT STYLE=font-family: Times New Roman, Times, Serif; font-size: 11pt><BR>"
"497","Bruce Fund, Inc.</FONT></P>"
"498","<P STYLE=margin: 0>&nbsp;</P>"
"499","<P STYLE=margin: 0></P>"
"500","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify>In planning and performing our audit"
"501","of the financial statements of Bruce Fund, Inc. (the &ldquo;Fund&rdquo;) as of and for the year ended June 30, 2019, in accordance"
"502","with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States), we considered the Fund&rsquo;s internal control"
"503","over financial reporting, including controls over safeguarding securities, as a basis for designing audit procedures for the purpose"
"504","of expressing an opinion on the financial statements and to comply with the requirements of Form N-CEN, but not for the purpose"
"505","of expressing an opinion on the effectiveness of the Fund&rsquo;s internal control over financial reporting. Accordingly, we express"
"506","no such opinion.</P>"
"507","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify>&nbsp;</P>"
"508","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify>Management of the Fund is responsible"
"509","for establishing and maintaining effective internal control over financial reporting. In fulfilling this responsibility, estimates"
"510","and judgments by management are required to assess the expected benefits and related costs of controls. A fund&rsquo;s internal"
"511","control over financial reporting is a process designed to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting"
"512","and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles."
"513","A fund&rsquo;s internal control over financial reporting includes those policies and procedures that (1) pertain to the maintenance"
"514","of records that, in reasonable detail, accurately and fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions of the assets of the fund;"
"515","(2) provide reasonable assurance that transactions are recorded as necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in accordance"
"516","with generally accepted accounting principles, and that receipts and expenditures of the fund are being made only in accordance"
"517","with authorizations of management and directors of the fund; and (3) provide reasonable assurance regarding prevention or timely"
"518","detection of unauthorized acquisition, use, or disposition of the fund&rsquo;s assets that could have a material effect on the"
"519","financial statements.</P>"
"520","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify>&nbsp;</P>"
"521","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify>Because of its inherent limitations,"
"522","internal control over financial reporting may not prevent or detect misstatements. Also projections of any evaluation of effectiveness"
"523","to future periods are subject to the risk that controls may become inadequate because of changes in conditions, or the degree of"
"524","compliance with policies and procedures may deteriorate.</P>"
"525","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify>&nbsp;</P>"
"526","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify>A deficiency in internal control over"
"527","financial reporting exists when the design or operation of a control does not allow management or employees, in the normal course"
"528","of performing their assigned functions, to prevent or detect misstatements on a timely basis. A material weakness is a deficiency,"
"529","or a combination of deficiencies, in internal control over financial reporting, such that there is a reasonable possibility that"
"530","a material misstatement of the fund&rsquo;s annual or interim financial statements will not be prevented or detected on a timely"
"531","basis.</P>"
"532","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify>&nbsp;</P>"
"533","<P STYLE=font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify></P>"
"534","<TABLE CELLPADDING=4 CELLSPACING=0 STYLE=border-collapse: collapse; font: 11pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; width: 100%>"
